The Southern Pyramid

The Southern Pyramid is the Moon Sovereign's counter-monument: an inverted
theology in architecture. What appears from the surface to be a modest
funerary complex is only the anchor point of an immense downward-engineered
state crypt, descending through seven tiers consecrated to aspects of death.

The Moon Sovereign, twin sibling and bitter rival of the Sand Sovereign,
rejected the Solar Court's doctrine that sunlight was law made visible.
Instead, the Moon Sovereign declared that true authority lay below, in the
underworld's root-systems of death that the Solar Court had tried to
domesticate. Each descending tier binds a death-function as administrative
domain:

  Silence  - suppression of dissent and witness control
  Decay    - managed ruin and reclamation from the dead
  Shadow   - surveillance through concealment
  Bone     - genealogy and legitimacy through remains
  Venom    - punishment refined to chemical efficiency
  Fire     - irreversible judgment and purification
  Void     - sovereign exception beyond all rite and law

These seven aspects systematically invert the Solar Court's seven virtues
of kingship. Each tier was designed to demonstrate that the Solar Court's
virtues were merely domesticated versions of death forces that the underworld
controlled more completely.

The volcanic glass lake at the nadir was designed as a controlled interface
with the anti-light source. The Moon Sovereign believed the Black Sun Shard
was not alien but a natural emanation of the underworld. Rather than contain
it, the Sovereign sought to learn its grammar.

The Eclipsed Tongues, the Moon Sovereign's theological faction, survived the
pyramid's sealing and merged with the Jackal Synod of the Eastern Desert,
injecting underworld-descent theology into what had been a purely solar cult.
Modern Synod members who speak of 'the eclipse that cleanses' unknowingly
channel Moon Sovereign doctrine filtered through centuries of corruption.
